  "robot_info_version": "0.2",

  "name": "Cortex Harness",
  "tagline": "A forkable AI-agent framework on the Mnemo Cortex memory layer. Pick a business vertical, edit one config file, build, and run.",
  "summary": "Cortex Harness turns the Mnemo Cortex memory layer into a memory-backed agent you can ship for a specific business. Fork it, set business.name + business.vertical in one config file, and the compiler renders a self-contained runnable workspace: brain lanes (identity, rules, playbooks) with placeholders filled in, a Mnemo Cortex backend config carrying a business-specific rule-set (persona), an MCP client config scoped to the tools you turned on, and launch scripts. Five verticals ship in the box (small-business, ecommerce, art-studio, writing, day-trading); adding your own is a folder. The engine is dependency-light Python (PyYAML only): config -> tool loader -> compiler -> CLI. Mnemo Cortex is a cloned dependency, not vendored. Custom verticals for a specific business are the natural paid-service extension.",
  "backstory": "Mnemo Cortex gives an agent persistent memory, but every business that wants to use it has to wire the same three things by hand: the agent's brain/identity, a rule-set for how cautious it should be, and which memory tools to expose. Cortex Harness makes those three first-class and config-driven, so the path from 'I have a memory layer' to 'I have a memory-backed assistant for my business' is fork, pick a vertical, edit one file, build. It was built clean-room — a fresh agent given only Mnemo Cortex as a dependency and asked to design the framework from first principles — then reviewed and finalized against the rest of the Project Sparks stack.",
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "license": "MIT",
  "homepage": "https://projectsparks.ai/cortex-harness",
  "source": "https://github.com/GuyMannDude/cortex-harness",
  "contact": "guy@projectsparks.ai",
  "maintainer": "Project Sparks",

  "capabilities": [
    "Verticals — a business type is a folder under verticals/ with a vertical.yaml (title, recommended persona/profile, custom personas), a rules.md rule-set, and brain templates. Five ship in the box; _base/ is inherited by every vertical so a new one only states what's different.",
    "One-file configuration — set business.name, business.vertical, a tool profile, and (optionally) a persona in harness.config.yaml. Everything else is derived. Blank fields fall back to the vertical's recommended defaults.",
    "Tool loader — pick a profile (minimal / standard / full), then layer enable/disable. The loader validates each tool's prerequisites against your deployment and DROPS a tool (with a reason) if its prerequisite is missing — e.g. mnemo_share is dropped unless memory.isolation is shared; bus tools drop unless a bus is configured.",
    "Brain templates — markdown lanes with {{placeholder}} substitution rendered from your config. The rules and tools lanes are regenerated from live config on every build so they can never drift from what was actually compiled.",
    "Persona rule-sets — a vertical's persona compiles into a Mnemo Cortex persona block (preflight rigor, context bias, confidence threshold, whether speculation is allowed). The persona IS the business's rule-set.",
    "Deterministic compile — `harness build` writes build/<slug>/ with brain lanes, agentb.yaml, mcp.json, start.sh/.ps1, TOOLS.md, and a manifest.json. Re-runnable; edits to generated files are overwritten by design.",
    "CLI — list (verticals), doctor (environment readiness), plan (dry-run: enabled vs dropped tools, no writes), build (compile), run (build then launch the Mnemo Cortex backend)."
  ],

  "exposes": {
    // Cortex Harness is NOT itself an MCP server. It COMPILES a configuration
    // that wires the Mnemo Cortex MCP bridge. The tools below are the
    // memory-layer tools the harness can scope into a build's mcp.json /
    // TOOLS lane — they are served by Mnemo Cortex, not by the harness.
    "cli": [
      {"command": "python -m harness list", "purpose": "List the available verticals."},
      {"command": "python -m harness doctor", "purpose": "Check the environment is ready (Python, PyYAML, mnemo-cortex present, Node for the bridge)."},
      {"command": "python -m harness plan", "purpose": "Dry-run: show the persona and the tools that would be enabled vs dropped (with reasons). No files written."},
      {"command": "python -m harness build", "purpose": "Compile the configured business into build/<slug>/ — a self-contained runnable workspace."},
      {"command": "python -m harness run", "purpose": "Build, then launch the Mnemo Cortex memory backend for this business."}
    ],
    "compiles_tools_from": "Mnemo Cortex (via its MCP bridge): memory (mnemo_recall/search/save/share), facts (mnemo_fact_get/query/save/demote), brain lanes (read/list/write_brain_file), passport (behavioral observation), lifecycle (agent_startup/session_end). A build's tool set is the subset the business turned on."
  },

